						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the west wall of the Kṛishṇasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1544 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Krōdhin, Kārtika śu. 12.</hi> The year Krōdhin falling within the reign of Sadāśiva corresponds to <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1466</hi> and the details may be equated to <hi rend="bold">1544 A.D., October 27, (Monday).</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is badly damaged and seems to refer to some grant made in the Guntakaṇṭi-sīma.</p>						

						</summary>
